Foo Fighters - Wikipedia

en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foo_Fighters
Foo Fighters are a rock band formed in 1994 by former Nirvana drummer Dave Grohl. They have won 15 Grammy Awards and were inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2021.

foo | Meaning & Origin - Dictionary.com

www.dictionary.com/e/tech-science/foo/
Foo is a term used in computer programming to indicate a generic or unspecified value or object. It has no connection to the WWII graffiti "Foo was here" or the FUBAR acronym.

FOO | definition in the Cambridge English Dictionary - Cambridge Dictionary

dictionary.cambridge.org/us/dictionary/english/foo
Foo is a word for a friend or someone who is from your hometown or neighborhood, used especially by young Latinos to refer to or address a young Latino man who dresses and has his hair in a particular style. Learn more about the meaning, pronunciation and examples of foo in the Cambridge English Dictionary.
